Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's still early in the year and yet I caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.54,0:00:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, talk about bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.09,0:00:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we had made plans to play karuta cards at\NAyumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s place, Mitsuhiko and the others called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time, a boy named Masao, who's living on the\Nsame floor in Room 2806, and his parents interrupted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.93,0:00:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing those three via the video call, I saw\Nthrough the fact that they weren't his real parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.61,0:00:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And urged Mitsuhiko and the others to\Ncontact the police before«ending the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.49,0:00:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said something\Nlike that, is that really the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.49,0:00:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to confirm that, we have no\Nchoice but to barge into that family.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.20,0:00:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our excuse was to play karuta cards with Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.42,0:00:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.42,0:00:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite the fact that he bragged about being good\Nat grabbing karuta cards, he couldn't grab any!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He finally grabbed his first card marked with\Nni, but got into a tug-of-war with Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.76,0:01:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And insisted that "a hated child thrives better in\Nthe world" was his card—how bizarre is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.60,0:01:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.72,0:01:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was trying to use the karuta cards to tell us something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.81,0:01:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What might that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.65,0:01:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I Love You Miss Mystery —\hthe one now in an endless labyrinth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.24,0:01:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's embrace this love and solve the puzzle right now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.25,0:01:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all cases were men...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose-the invisible mysteries would he women.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A message in dire straits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.63,0:01:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the truth portrayed by the karuta cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.43,0:01:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.01,0:01:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.85,0:01:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.39,0:03:14.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.39,0:03:14.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,GRABBING KARUTA CARDS IN DIRE STRAITS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.48,0:03:19.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tsuki to support\NDifferent/as chalk and cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,atama kakushite shiri kakusazu\NTo hide your head but not your rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.37,0:03:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.20,0:03:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,oni ni kanabou\NLike carrying a big stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.37,0:03:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,GET!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next one...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.41,0:03:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ten shtru chi shiru\NHeaven knows and earth knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.58,0:03:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,uso kara deta makoto\NMany a true word is spoken in jest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only five cards left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.30,0:03:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.18,0:03:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hana yori\NPraise is not pudding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,GET!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.89,0:03:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My seventh card!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.65,0:03:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are only four cards left, and since you only have four cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means you can't beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.82,0:04:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.20,0:04:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} manages to take all four of the remaining\Ncards, he'd turn the tables and win.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.41,0:04:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mommy, restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The game is about to end, so just hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.21,0:04:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.96,0:04:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, Mommy will go with you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go to the restroom on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.60,0:04:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.56,0:04:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My child has claustrophobia, so he needs me by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.15,0:04:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take out that towel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.02,0:04:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ta o ru ke ga ni su wa ko\NThe towel with a horsehair crab from Lake Suwa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't do it without that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.70,0:04:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.03,0:04:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop saying selfish things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.91,0:04:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think about that mother and child?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think they're really related.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he said "Mommy, restroom" like a spoiled child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't call a bad person "Mommy", after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could also be that he was forced to call her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do think it's unusual for that mother\Nto stick around Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} nonstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.73,0:05:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if she's monitoring his every move\Nso that he can't try anything funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.99,0:05:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, were they indeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key to support or reject that theory is what Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} had...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ru and ko and ni and te...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.29,0:05:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those four cards might be our key.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what on earth does "ru ko ni te" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.54,0:05:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should rearrange these to form a word?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think we should.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.76,0:05:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first card he took was ni, but he deliberately\Nplaced it so that it's the third card from the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.47,0:05:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you mean this is the correct order?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.01,0:05:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:05:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His attempt to go to the restroom, as well\Nas evacuate the mother from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could be an effort to buy us time in order to solve this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't understand its meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we read it backwards, "te ni ko ru" won't work either
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to begin with, even if the mother and father are fakes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.95,0:06:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't figure out the reason why they'd\Nbe staying here, acting as his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.08,0:06:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they're kidnappers, they should've already moved to another place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they're robbers, they would've pretended\Nno one's home instead of letting us in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's call Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and ask him about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we do that, wouldn't we be able to know the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he's asleep because of his cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.14,0:06:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if that mother is really a fake, wouldn't it be dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.47,0:06:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.36,0:06:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's text him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he still has the strength to get up\Narid read my text, he'll reply soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.41,0:06:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he doesn't, it means he's still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you going to write in your email?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.86,0:07:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sequence of events leading to our visit to Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} suspected that those three people weren't\Nbiologically related just by looking at the video call...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.76,0:07:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he told us to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.63,0:07:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we had doubts about that deduction, so we asked the\Nneighbors of Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who's living in Room 2806.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.64,0:07:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lady in Room 2807 said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.60,0:07:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s family just moved in and that she\Nhasn't met with his parents, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did say that she knew the previous resident of this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, formerly employed by the Isobe Corporation,\Nwhich is now under suspicion of tax evasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.79,0:07:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the name was Uemura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.87,0:07:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mister from Room 2805 also said\Nhe'd never seen Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.16,0:07:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, he also said that he saw Producer\NHida from Nichiuri TV about two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.51,0:07:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He saw the producer going into Room 2806.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.35,0:08:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that producer later had a traffic accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.64,0:08:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was in critical condition until yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.94,0:08:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The matching statement of the two neighbors was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is a prankster...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a big liar on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, we came to Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s place to ascertain the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With an excuse of playing karuta cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} left us the four cards he took—ru, ko, ni, te...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While going to the restroom with the mother, and here we are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.71,0:08:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we write about the towel as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.72,0:08:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said "I can't go to the restroom without the towel\Nwith a horsehair crab from Lake Suwa on it".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.43,0:08:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sending...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.19,0:08:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, that was a very mismatched towel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:08:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you'll never find horsehair crabs in a lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.36,0:08:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Horsehair crabs only live in the sea, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:08:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,su u/a ko\NLake Suwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ke ga ni\NHorsehair crab...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ta o ru\NTowel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't do it without that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.05,0:09:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what he meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.93,0:09:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You already figured something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.52,0:09:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you just showed the same expression as Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.94,0:09:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How rude...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.27,0:09:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's true that I've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.03,0:09:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he was right all along!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.49,0:09:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was right, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the man and woman just now really are bad guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretending to be Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s real parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're up to no good, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.13,0:09:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how did you figure that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.26,0:10:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the karuta cards Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four cards—ru, ko, ni, and te—told us so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.27,0:10:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, in order to only collect those four cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had positioned those cards beforehand so\Nthat they would've been easy for him to grab.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.86,0:10:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he headed to the restroom with the\Nwoman who was faking as his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.74,0:10:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all to have the rest of us figure out...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "ru ko ni te" code he had constructed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.33,0:10:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, unfortunately the first ni card he tried to grab...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.46,0:10:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the first to take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.17,0:10:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, I'll never let you have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.63,0:10:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this ni card is my card!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.97,0:10:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Resulted in a tug-of-war with Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.93,0:10:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "ru ko ni te".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.60,0:10:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} told us, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.65,0:10:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key to solving the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By saying "I can't do it without that!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:10:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.94,0:10:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The towel with the horsehair crab from Lake Suwa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.41,0:11:05.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Lake Suwa, horsehair crab, and towel all have three syllables.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.41,0:11:05.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,su wa ko ke ga ni ta o ru
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Change the middle syllable of each—wa, ga, and o...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.95,0:11:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Into the particles wa, ga, and o...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.04,0:11:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And think along those lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.63,0:11:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are "particles", anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean "party girls"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.80,0:11:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are words between nouns or in connective sentences\Nthat show relation or attach meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.35,0:11:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:28.97,Signs,,0,0,0,,GENTA{\rHonorifics - Signs}-KUN{\r} IS A BOY
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:28.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,wa\NGenta{\rHonorifics - Signs}-kun{\r} Is a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.14,0:11:28.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"su wa ko" should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.27,0:11:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"su IS ko"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So isn't it telling us that su IS represented by ko?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.15,0:11:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, "ke ga ni"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.03,0:11:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Means to treat ke AS if it were ni, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.20,0:11:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, "ta o ru"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Means ta was changed INTO ru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So taking that into account...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try reading the four characters—ru, ko, ni, te.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.71,0:11:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving the last te, which doesn't fall under any of the rules, as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We make the first ru INTO ta...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.93,0:12:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next ko IS actually su...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.14,0:12:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if we think of the third card, ni, AS ke...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.94,0:12:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means ".HELP"!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.94,0:12:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:20.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two pretending to be Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s real parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are bad guys scheming who-knows-what.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.03,0:12:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is appealing to us for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.53,0:12:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.70,0:12:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This wouldn't be another lie again, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's got a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible this could be an elaborate prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.58,0:12:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would he have used a code like this that he couldn't\Nbe sure we'd be able to solve as a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a code made so that the woman\Nfaking as his mother wouldn't catch on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.68,0:12:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, that child...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.93,0:12:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we were about to be turned away at the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.85,0:12:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.31,0:13:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s real parents be, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know about his father, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as his mother, I can make a fair guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Said something odd besides "the towel of the\Nhorsehair crab from Lake Suwa," didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, didn't he say he was good at karuta\Ncards, but turned out to really suck at playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason for that was just because he had\Nto collect those four cards and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was going to the restroom and said,\N"Mommy, restroom!" in a spoiled tone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was also only because he had wanted to get that\Nwoman away from here and have us solve the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.90,0:13:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, even if he hadn't deliberately said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that woman would've\Naccompanied Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.40,0:13:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.99,0:13:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had let Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} leave by himself,\Nhe might've taken the chance and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.95,0:13:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he purposely said "Mommy, restroom!" in order to make us...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Connect that phrase with the "HELP" we figured out earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.42,0:14:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Connect them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.13,0:14:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.92,0:14:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.80,0:14:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.59,0:14:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kid's mother!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.43,0:14:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They locked her in the restroom!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.47,0:14:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.01,0:14:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we lack solid proof, if we think of it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.14,0:14:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd make sense that the man faking as his father\Nhas been inside the restroom this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.40,0:14:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.98,0:14:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should've just called Detective Takagi in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.66,0:14:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as that cold-ridden detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must be sweating up a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.04,0:14:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I brought a change of clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.33,0:14:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.71,0:14:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with that fever...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could you have gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.38,0:14:49.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.38,0:14:49.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,I'll be back soon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.38,0:14:49.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.55,0:14:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:14:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.02,0:15:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are we going to save her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mother who is locked in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd have to do something about that woman\Nwho's pretending to be his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.03,0:15:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if we don't decide on a strategy soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll be back before we know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.41,0:15:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.74,0:15:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to rescue or capture anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.83,0:15:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we need to do is finish playing this\Nround of karuta cards and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we won't do anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.17,0:15:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon after we leave, we'll call Detective\NTakagi and explain the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And get him to come and save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.89,0:15:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, if you all wanted to show Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And have the four of us make a reckless\Ngamble, that's another story altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.52,0:15:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.86,0:15:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose cell phone is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.87,0:15:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wonder whose it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.08,0:15:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.62,0:15:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not Ayumi's, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.01,0:16:11.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very keen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.38,0:16:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.05,0:16:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left it there while the line was still connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.26,0:16:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I was on the other end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, I know full well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.81,0:16:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you aren't just normal brats...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But bothersome pests that can't be allowed to leave here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And where is Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's keeping his mother company as\NI tied him up in the restroom as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, at any rate, you guys will soon\Njoin them in that same restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.80,0:16:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, girl, with the hair band.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tie your friends up withthat sticky tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.43,0:17:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all that's done, I'll tie you up myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.93,0:17:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you don't like that idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.77,0:17:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have other ways of rendering you immobile!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.86,0:17:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as we finish our business here, we'll leave you all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're lucky and the real man of this household\Ncomes back from his business trip early...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may even be able to save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.09,0:17:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, what could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.67,0:17:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That "business" of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there's no telling, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.39,0:17:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hurry and answer it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could that be...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.60,0:17:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm from the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.48,0:17:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this Uemura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Room 2806?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:17:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.86,0:18:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding a registered mail you sent for delivery...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The addressee was unavailable, so we were unable to deliver it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.29,0:18:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.08,0:18:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they've moved...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, since this is registered mail, may I have\Nyour permission to directly return it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, I'm buzzing you up now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.30,0:18:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he'd come for us after he read the email we sent...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.81,0:18:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I've finally-figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you two are trying to destroy evidence\Npertaining to tax evasion!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.82,0:18:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sender of that registered mail was the\Nprevious resident of this apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.86,0:18:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one named Uemura, who was a former employee of the\NIsobe Corporation, now under suspicion of tax evasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.38,0:18:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the registered mail are\Nprobably whistleblower documents...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.87,0:18:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or account books with evidence of tax evasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.00,0:18:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was sent approximately two weeks ago—in exchange\Nfor a reward—to a producer at Nichiuri TV named Hida.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:19:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The employee planned to move from here and go into hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that producer ended up in a car accident, and couldn't\Nreceive the registered mail due to being hospitalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.02,0:19:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the post office holds on to mail for more or less ten days...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.48,0:19:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You calculated the time of its return...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And plotted to pose as Uemura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who had lived\Nhere before, and snatch away that registered mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what happened to that Uemura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.87,0:19:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably confined somewhere else, or already murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.29,0:19:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And made to look like an accident,\Nsimilar to the Nichiuri TV producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.67,0:19:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I was right on the mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.97,0:19:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, he's at the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.22,0:19:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get it from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.19,0:19:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, as for what to do with you lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.82,0:20:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose we'll decide after we've checked out the registered mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.33,0:20:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.25,0:20:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.89,0:20:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you can't ente-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cuff that woman, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.56,0:20:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.64,0:20:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.73,0:20:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the woman from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.70,0:20:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put her to sleep with my tranquilizer watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she's being handcuffed right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.66,0:20:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By Detective Takagi who's dressed in that postal worker getup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.25,0:20:58.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, if you're asking why Detective\NTakagi is dressed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You read the email I sent and deduced that they\Nwere after the returned registered mail, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, how did you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.55,0:21:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That those two-people weren't really Masao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you only see them through the video phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah,-it's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw their hairlines, I noticed only\NMasao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} had a widow's peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.48,0:21:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The widow's peak is a dominant trait, so parents without\Nwidow's peaks could never have given birth to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.58,0:21:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you guys all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.54,0:21:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bad guys have been caught, so you can relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.59,0:21:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope you learn from this and don't tell pointless lies ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.18,0:21:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll never tell another lie as long as I live!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.22,0:21:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, that better not have been a lie just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.15,0:23:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so the president was indeed arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.15,0:23:28.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,2 Days Later
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.53,0:23:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since he even went as far as to hire those two\Nto destroy the evidence, it only stands to reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.37,0:23:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it looks like Uemura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who had\Nbeen confined has also been rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.12,0:23:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this great?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.71,0:23:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.04,0:23:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.17,0:23:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All caught a cold from me... did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.38,0:23:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My cold is completely gone, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.72,0:23:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, take care not to catch a cold!
